<title>USA: CPI Aerostructures in Nordam settlement.</title>
<headline>CPI Aerostructures in Nordam settlement.</headline>
<dateline>EDGEWOOD, N.Y. 1996-11-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>CPI Aerostructures Inc said on Friday it reached a $750,000 cash settlement with the Nordam Corp regarding that company's partial termination of a contract to supply parts for the Hawker 1000 aircraft.</p>
<p>The settlement will cause CPI to take a $370,000 non-cash charge in the fourth quarter. In spite of the provision, CPI said it expected to post earnings for the quarter, completing its most profitable year since 1992.</p>
